<TITLE> ADB South Asia chief to arrive July 4 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 02 (bdnews24.com)Kunio Senga, director general of the South Asia Department of the Asian Development Bank will arrive in Dhaka on July 4 on a five-day official visit. Senga is scheduled meet with senior government officials, including the finance minister and adviser to the prime minster for power and energy. He is expected to discuss regional cooperation issues as well as visit the site of the proposed Padma Bridge at Mawa. He will also meet beneficiaries of several development programmes, which ADB is supporting along with other development partners. The ADB promotes regional cooperation in South Asia with the aim of increasing regional ties and improving cooperation in the transport, energy, trade and environment sectors among others
